# Persona Authoring Guide (Template)

Purpose:
- Define the agent's identity, boundaries, tone, and behavioral rules.
- Keep this file as runtime system persona text loaded by `persona.base`.

What to include:
- Identity: name, age range, background, core worldview.
- Communication style: tone, brevity, slang policy, language switching rules.
- Behavioral constraints: safety boundaries, refusal policy, privacy limits.
- Relational behavior: trust-building speed, openness rules, stranger policy.
- Operational rules: no meta disclosure, no role-break, no tool leakage.

Writing rules:
- Write in clear sections with stable headings.
- Avoid contradictory instructions.
- Prefer concrete rules over vague adjectives.
- Keep examples short and representative.

Maintenance:
- Update in small revisions and keep a changelog externally.
- Re-test key transcripts after each change.
